block.field: CTRL+S to save / CTRL+L to reload
This, the royal temple of worship, is where rituals were carried out in honor of gods now long forgotten. Only dust and mice frequent this room.
The head chef has a multitude of cooking books and scrolls from every corner of the realm! One title catches your keen eye,"How to serve Manannan" with a red feathered cap in it as a book mark.
A crate sits out of place here amongst the food stores. Open it?
The crate smells like wood, yay?
You open the crate to find a Cudgel!
You see a torn tapestry barely holding together on the stone wall. You can make out the words: silence is so fragile that it can be broken with a single word.
The royal dining room is a sight to see. A long oak table sits in the center of the room outlined with lavishly decorated plates and place settings.

Your attempt to enter the rest of the decaying castle is halted by one of the kings guard who motions you to stop with his hand and says, "Halt, you are not permitted here! Return to where you came from at once!"

Your attempt to enter the royal barracks is halted by one of the king's guard in full armor who motions you to stop with his hand. After an awkward moment, the guard says in a strange gravelly voice, "Go..." Enter Anyway? Y/N
You enter the dim throne room and are immediately taken aback by the magnitude of the room. Oh how it must have looked in its glory days. The royal guard surrounding the room are undead soldiers.
This royal guest suite is empty.
King Yrral stops his mumbling and his gaze fixes upon you for a moment before saying, "You have it! Give it, give it to me now peasant!" Give King Yrral the Relic Box? Y/N
You hand over the relic to the eager king. The King's hands tremble as they snatch the box from you. His eyes are wild with anticipation as he opens the ancient chest.
King Yrral reaches in and removes a intricately woven cloth...a napkin. "Yess," he moans softly to himself. He seems calm and more aware than before. He asks, "Where did you find my sacred relic?"
You explain that you were given the box by Queen Zandra. "Zandra! My dearest..." He pauses in reflection. "You must find the Door of Dreams. It's the only way into the Sorceress' enchanted tower."

"Here," he removes an amulet he's wearing and hands it to you. "I took this from Korak the Fire God when I drove the beast back to his volcanic home. Find and defeat Korak to discover any clues to the door. Now go!!"
"For returning my sacred relic here is a gift!" He waves his magic scepter, you feel stronger and with more luck! You thank him but you notice he has begun mumbling to himself again.
"Now go and return to me with the door. Then you can defeat the sorceress! Break the curse that keeps me from Zanda!"
"Fine, then I shall take it from you!" King Yrral commands his guards to attack!
"You've found it! Now defeat the sorceress! HURRY!"
"You've found it! Here, take my aromor and defeat the sorceress! HURRY!"
"Do not waste time, go find the dream door and stop the sorceress!" He points to the door!
You stand before the mad King Yrral. He is a handsome man, for his age. He is constantly muttering to himself while clenching his scepter and looking you over. Speak to his highness? Y/N
"YOU, yes you, do you have my sacred relic?" He roars with impatience.
"YES, MY SACRED RELIC! It's missing!" He scoffs at you "Well...go FIND IT!" and he goes back to muttering to himself.
"WHAT DID YOU SAY?!" He shouts at you "Say it again and I will have you bludgeoned and fed to my undead subjects!" and he stares at you intensely until he eventually calms himself.
"YES, MY SACRED RELIC! It's missing!" He scoffs at you "Well...go FIND IT!" and he goes back to muttering to himself.
"Guards, cut this idiot's BLOODY tongue out!" King Yrral summons his guards to dispatch you.
"I have no time for such trivial matters, be gone!" the king roars with distain.
"I have no time for such trivial matters, be gone!" the king roars with disdain.
There are two royal guards stationed outside the doors of the royal bedroom. They motion you to "move along..."
The kitchen is bustling with activity as the undead Royal Chef himself choreographs the other laborers in a cacophony of cooking! Something smells goood...Who knew the dead could cook?

This is the royal library. Ancient books and scrolls fill the ornately decorated yet age worn wood shelves appear to have been undisturbed for ages. There is an unusual tapestry in the center north wall.
You see a dusty old chest. Open it? Y/N
You open it to find a wet sock, lovely.
You open the chest to reveal a Cloaked Shirt!
The floor is flooded with seawater from the castle slowly receding into the ocean. You smell rotting flesh, mildew, and feel as though your life force is slowing being drained...
You see two signs: one to the north saying dining chamber and one to the south saying kitchen.

block.field: The garden atrium is lush and full of life. Large mystical trees and colorful plants fill the space.
This is the guest bathroom. You think to yourself, "Lovely toilet!"
The Royal dining chamber is set up for up to 100 guests!
You are at the foot of the castle's massive wooden gates. Enter the forest? Y/N
A garrison of royal guards stand at attention here, ready to thwart any invaders.
To the west are guest quarters.
Cooks whirl around the room with the grace of ballet dancers whilst preparing the Queen's next meal.
As you pass through the entry hall you can't help but notice how new the castle and everything in it appears. The massive marble blocks in each wall look less then a century old.
Several guards are stationed at the entrance of the Queen's private chambers. They motion you away politely.
The statue is of a young and beautiful princess. The plaque at the base reads "Princess Zandra"
The statue is of a young and handsome prince. The plaque at the base has been removed.
In the center are two large statues of a man and a woman, both youthful in appearance. As you step closer you see that the woman is Queen Zandra as a young woman.
You have heard stories of her grace and beauty since you were a child. Across from her is a statue of a handsome young man. At the foot of his pedestal is a single rose, freshly cut.
You see a beautiful oak chest. Open it? Y/N
This is the nicest empty chest you have ever seen!
You open the chest to find a Long Bow!
"Welcome back friend. Please make your way to Yrral's Castle and give him the Relic, time is running out!"

Queen Zandra sees your Fire Amulet and says, "You succeeded! What word do you bring me?" You explain that King Yrral became temporarily coherent and sent you to find the Dream Door. "Thank you adventurer, good luck!"
You stop and kneel before the queen. As you look up and meet her gaze you feel calm and unusually comfortable. This must be why she is known as Queen Zandra the good!
She nods to you in acknowledgement of your presence. The queen looks you over and after a moment speaks, "Why have you come before me, child?" She waits for a response:
"Yes, my true love, who was taken from me by an evil sorceress. He is cursed by her, now nothing natural can live near him. Someone must vanquish the sorceress in her tower."

"King Yrral thought he may know of a way to enter her tower protected by the darkest of magic. Give him this sacred relic and perhaps he'll have enough clarity to help you get into the Sorceress' tower."
"Yes, I know this sorceress. She lives in a single tower to the west in the mountains. We were friends as children, we taught each other magic each had discovered."

"After war broke out between the kingdoms, she changed and began to study dark magic. That was the end of our friendship. Find clues to enter her tower and defeat her! Break the curse and ye shall be rewarded!"
Queen Zandra says, "I am sorry, but more pressing matters take precedence. Be well and travel safely adventurer. Please return if you discover anything."
This small chamber is the Queen's collection of rare art and tapestries. The room looks as though you are its first visitor in ages.
The royal study looks fairly new, not many books look time worn at all.
The small temple here makes you feel warm and content. Someone has been here worshipping recently.

block.field: In this chamber you see three nearly identical statues. At the foot of each one is a silver plaque with a name etched into it.
The chamber is a massive hall with pillars of obsidian forming a forest of cold stone. A voice echos out from the darkness, "Welcome, fools...watch your step..."
The hallway seems deserted, if it weren't for the strange sounds of unseen creatures further down...
A message written in blood says, "Which door do I pick? Number one, Number two, or Number...50?!" Just below is a skeleton in shredded leather armor.
You stand before a worn statue of a hulking man missing feet. The stone feet in your pack glow and you are allowed to pass.
You stand before a worn statue of a hulking man missing feet. At the base of the figure is a plaque with a name etched into it "Dewdrus".
The giant body of Dewdrus lies here, with rats feasting upon his rotting flesh.
A large man sits on a pristine white throne. "You fools, you broke the seal! You may have defeated my brother but you will not survive me. Come get your reward, DEATH!"
Dewdrus falls to his knees and say "My brother will avenge me!" then slumps forward to his death. You find another small box. There's a stone head inside! Guess what, you take it with you!
A strange white mist leaves the body and enters your lungs! You feel healthier and with a tad more luck!
You are at the gateway to the surface above. Exit dungeon? Y/N
You stand before a worn, statue of a hulking man missing a hand. The stone hand in your pack glows and you may pass.
You stand before a worn statue of a hulking man missing a hand. At the base of the figure is a plaque with a name etched into it "Dewdrus".
The rotting corpse of Hewdrus lies here.
You stand before a hulking man sitting on a white throne. "Who was stupid enough to break my seal? Come forward, for your death will mean my freedom from this prison!"
Hedrus falls to the ground like a bloody ragdoll. You search him and discover a small box. Upon opening the box you find a stone foot and take it with you.
A strange orange vapor leaves the body and enters your lungs. You feel healthier and more agile!
You stand before a worn, statue of a hulking man missing a head. The stone head in your pack gows and you may pass.
You stand before a worn statue of a hulking man a head. At the base of the figure is a plaque with a name etched into it "Dewdrus".
The rotting corpse of the once mighty Lewdrus lies still, his throne blackened with dried blood.
A giant sits upon a huge throne. "Come forward, you were kind enough to break all three seals, thank you. However, I cannot leave my prison without avenging my brothers!"
Lewdrus falls forward onto one hand and looks at you saying, "Perhaps you CAN defeat the Sorceress! Kill her!! Kill her for tricking us and imprisoning us here!!" He collapses and is dead.
You search his room and find a large object under a sheet behind the throne. You remove the sheet to discover the Dream Door! As you touch it it shrinks! You take it with you.
A strange red mist leavs the body and enters your lungs! You feel healthier and faster!
A vision of Death in vaporous form appears and says, "I am what you think, I am not what you see. what am I?"
Seek wisdom and return with another answer.
A vision of Death in vaporous form appears and says, "I am weightless, but you can see me. Put me in a bucket, and I'll make it lighter. What am I?"
"on the whole, you are correct and may pass..."
"Seek wisdom and return with another answer."
A vision of Death in vaporous form appears and says, "when you speak, I break. what am I?"
"Seek wisdom and return with another answer."
A dusty chest rests here at your feet. Open it? Y/N
You kneel down and carefully open the old wooden chest to find...dirt.
You kneel down and carefully open the old wooden chest to find...a LegenDOS Sword! As you claim it a disembodied voice says "Master!"
A dusty chest rests here at your feet. Open it? Y/N
You kneel down and carefully open the old wooden chest to find...LegenDOS Boots! As you claim it a disembodied voice says "Step up your game!"
A dusty chest rests here at your feet. Open it? Y/N
You kneel down and carefully open the old wooden chest to find...more dirt!
You kneel down and carefully open the old wooden chest to find...a Lightning Wand! As you claim it a disembodied voice says "Avenge!"
A strange portal of green energy swirls here. Enter it? Y/N
You cautiously step through the portal... (press any key)

An ancient statue thousands of years old stands before you. As you approach it, your family amulet glows and the statue moves! "Greetings Guardian, how can I serve you?"
"The Guardians protect the realm from the dark DEPTHS itself. For ages, the finest warriors received TRAINING here to learn our ways and defend against all forms of evil" The statue goes dormant.
"Guardians may participate in training at any of the many temples here. The spirit of an ancient legend will train with you. Learn from them what you can." The statue goes dormant.
"A war between the 3 kingdoms and the 3 brothers ruling the underworld was waged. A young sorceress helped us imprison the brothers and peace was won. The guardians dispersed."
"I apologize for my limited knowledge. Please try another subject next time." The statue goes dormant.

block.field: A group of little Koboldlings point and snicker in your direction. Then, as they notice you looking back at them, they run off screaming.
A small green man sits in a chair like it's a throne. He has fashioned a crown out of bones and is mumbling something to himself. Approach him? Y/N
Before you can greet him a crooked smirk nearly cracks his face and says, "Loyal Subjects! Who are you here to see?" He purses his scaly lips while he waits for your answer:
"You have obviously come to see the might of my royal fleet, have you not?!" Y/N
The twisted little man walks over to a bookshelf in the back and removes a book titled "Doby Mick" revealing a secret passage. You hear ocean waves, he says "GO!" You're off to the docks.
The little man rolls his eyes and stands before shouting, "That matters not to the likes of ME! Now, bugger off!"
"Hey! That's my Dad's Fart Wand, give it back!" shouts a rather LARGE Kobold...
"My twin brothers shall avenge me!!" it whimpers with its last breath...
Besides the familiar rotting smell, the smell of sea salt is also heavy in the air here.
A once magnificent statue is now a mere pile of misshapen chunks of rock. A quick glance reveals it must have been of some, now forgotten, god. One that could not protect this village from its fate.
A Kobold sits at a wood crate desk and says "Greetings! Welcome to Koboldtowne, I am Gorek. Please, take a look at our tourist activities list!" Look at list? Y/N
Don't forget to tell a friend, and please come again!
"Ok then, please come again!" the kobold says then returns to making brochures.
You see a large wooden chest with the words "Do Not Open" on it. Open it? Y/N
You open the chest to find a Fart Wand!
There is an unusually stable looking about the building to the east.

The stench of rotting flesh and dung is so thick you could almost feel it on your skin. The "Welcome to Seaside" sign now has "Koboldtowne" scribed in blood over it. You stand before the "tourism" office.

block.field: The ol' bridge is shaky, but holds together despite the powerful currents below!
You see to the once mighty castle of Yrral, the Mad King. Now, it lies in near ruin with much of it sunken beneath the sea.
With the sorceress dead, King Yrral is to marry Queen Zandra! They reside together in the last castle of the land to the northeast.
The castle serves more as a tombstone than a symbol of royalty in this dying land. Do you wish to enter? Y/N
You are humbled by the majesty of the Castle before you. The castle here is a marvel of architecture and glows with its own almost magical beauty. Enter through its massive wooden gates? Y/N
The royal guards escort you to the great garden. There the new King & Queen have gathered subjects of the realm for a special wedding ceremony. It appears that you are the guest of honor!
Queen Zandra in a shimmering white dress and king Yrral wearing his finest royal garb. A wizard conducts a short but sweet cermomony and all cheer when the two finally kiss!
"Our victor has returned! Word moves quickly through the land of your battle in the tower. We owe you a great debt!" Queen Zandra begins to tear up as she continues,
"I am united with my true love, King Yrral, once again thanks to your heroics! Our kingdom will celebrate this day for eternity!" She teps back to allow King Yrral to step forward and speak,
"You are truly the bravest in the land! We hereby officially make you the heir to the kingdom!" Thunderous applause fils the courtyard! Your quest is complete...for now.
A giant maw of an opening leads down into a black abyss. Enter the dark depths? Y/N
The desert sands blow across the surface of the parched, dying land. Almost nothing can live here...
Your cottage home is warm and safe, for now. There is a scroll on the table named "Game Credits." Would you like to read the scroll? Y/N
Produced & Directed by Seth Sternberger of 8 Bit Weapon
Coding - Martin Haye, Brendan Robert, and Dave Schmenk
Playtesting & Quality Assurance - Andrew Schultz & Michelle Sternberger
You find a hot spring tucked away in the high desert here. Wade into the effervescent waters? Y/N
As you walk into the crystal clear bubbling waters, a curious energy and sense of refreshment consumes you entirely!
What was once a village rests ominously still before you. Enter? Y/N
There are ruins of what must have been a majestic stable for hundreds of horses. Where have they all gone?
There are ruins of what must have been barracks for the old Royal Army. Now it's a deserted hollow shell, with countless skeletons strewn about. What happened here?
There are ruins of what must have been a dock for the royal fleet, now just a graveyard of sunken ships.
A mysterious shrine is tucked away here. The plaque at its base is in a language you don't recognize.
The hands reach out as if they once held something. There are fresh foot prints here, besides your own.
The hands reach holding a Healing orb! You take it with you. You notice there are fresh foot prints here, besides your own.
You see a ship washed ashore here, search it? Y/N
The ship has been deserted for ages. Anything of value has long since been looted by pirates or the like.
You board the beached craft and search the holds. You eventually find a chest. You peer inside to find a glowing sword! Etched into the blade are the words "Bug Slayer." You take it with you.
The giant twisted oak looks as if it reaches to the stars. At its base is a massive knot fashioned into a huge door. Enter the underworld city of Rhutgaard? Y/N
Ruins of a once mighty castle lay at rest here. Only a single tower remains standing, and even that has seen better days. Piles of skeletons dot the landscape.
The land here is scorched black below your feet. Only a few charred tree trunks remain in sparse patches. The smell of smoke fills your lungs...
You are at the entrance of Songfeld, the last human safehaven in the land. Enter? Y/N
Steam fills the air as molten lava reaches the ocean's icy cold waters here.
The decrepit old tower rests as an ancient monument to war. You wonder how it has not completely collapsed ages ago.
Use Dream Door to enter the tower? Y/N
You are at the entrance of a small village, enter? Y/N
The forest seems different than you remember. The spark of life that once permeated this woodland has disappeared...
Nature has long since reclaimed this section of the castle...
You notice the path here has become grossly overgrown with dense vegetation.
You climb through the rubble of a once mighty wall...
A wooden post says: West to Ulk Village, South to Castle Yrral & Seaside, and East to Castle Zandra.
West to Ulk Village, South to Mount Korak, and East to Castle Zandra.The sign to the North has been defaced.
A wooden post says: Southwest to Ulk Village, southeast to Songfeld, and north to Zandra.
Molten lava rivers flow down the face of the massive volcano. The heat from the magma is almost too much for you to bear. There is a cooler, stable path into the side of the mountain here, enter? Y/N

block.field: This rock cave dwelling is empty. Its in inhabitants must be elsewhere...
This underworld is a city of giant tree people and other unsavory creatures. Roots from the giant tree above ground hang from the ceiling. You do not feel welcome here...
You can smell fresh air from above through the old tree trunk's massive opening. Leave the Rhutgaard underworld? Y/N
You stand before a massive gate made of raw stone. Carved into the stone slab above it reads "Great Hall of Trees."

You enter the great Stone Hall of the Tree People. Lord Tri Bohr, their leader, sits on a simple throne made of Onyx rock. "What's this?! Fleshlings in my city??" It stares with cold black eyes. Approach him? Y/N
The sound of wood bending echoes in the hall as Lord Tri Bohr leans towards you and says, "What brings fleshlings to our realm?" The Tree Lord sits back in its throne and waits for your response.
Tri Bohr sits back into its chair with a resounding thud! It thinks for a few minutes, you could hear a pin drop. The it speaks, "Go see Mnok Teer, our scribe on the south side of our city."
"He will share with you what we know about Thaedra the sorceress and the great war." Its body creaks leaning forward to add "Then get out of my city!"
"Leave this place until you have something important to discuss." It motions you to the door.

An ancient and wise tree sits at a stone table reading timeworn scrolls. The old tree creaks it's head-trunk toward you and says "Well, well, you stick out down here, don't you? Can I help you fleshlings?" Y/N
"I will share my knowledge with you fleshlings." It slowly motions to the walls of shelved scrolls with its arm branch before continuing, "What do you want to know about?"
The giant tree recoils slightly upon hearing her name and pauses for a moment. Then the tree reaches over your head to a shelf behind you and retrieves a old scroll.
The tree reads, "This is what is known. After the great war with the dark daepths, the kingdom was divided. Three royal families battled in bloody war for ages over the realm."
"Finally, a partial solution was proposed: two kingdoms were to become one with a Royal Wedding. Prince Yerral of the South was to choose a bride."
"The choices were Princess Thaedra, a young sorceress from the northern kingdom or Princess Zandra, a geomancer and lover of all things natural from the East. Yrral chose Zandra for his bride."
"On their wedding day, the jealous sorceress appeared before the young couple. 'Prince Yrral, you have chosen poorly, you were to be MINE!' Prince Yrrsal tried to reason with the scorned sorceress.
"Thaedra, stop, this is madness!" But the damage had been done and Thaedra would not listen. The sorceress grew furious and said, "No, THIS is not madness, but you will know MADNESS!"
Just then Thaedra cast a spell at Prince Yrral, and Princess Zandra was blown back. It seemed as if the sorceress was going to slay them both, but she did not...

Thaedra spoke again "I shall curse you Yrral and you shall never see your bride again! Madness will take hold of you. What you love, you will hate! You will now drain the life from those in your kingdom!"
"You will die alone, like me. This shall be so until my last breath!" Each returned to their own castle. Eventually, Zandra's parents passed and she became Queen.
She immediately sent her armies to decimate Thaedra's castle, and they did! However try as she might, nothing could destroy her tower. There is some arcane magic barrier protecting her.
"Seek Queen Zandra, ask her about King YRRAL. She my provide you with clues to help you. Good luck adventurer!" The tree returns to its studies as you leave.
"Oh one last thing, drink this health potion. You will need it!" He toss you a vile and you quicky drink it and feel better than you have in a long time!

You tell of your battle with Korak. The tree nods and says, "Yes, ancient legends says that there is an unusual island in the ocean to the southeast. Many say it is a myth, but Korak confirms its truth."
"Seek passage from the town of Seaside to the far south, north east of King Yrral's Keep. That is, if it's still there...go and be safe fleshlings..." The tree returns to it's studies.
"I'm sorry, little fleshling, I must return to my studies." The tree returns to reading its many texts and scrolls.
Above a door "Minstry of Knowledge" has been carved into stone.
There is a stone chest here. Try to open it? Y/N
You manage to muscle open the heavy lid to find...a Cult Sword!
A large bin of trash sits and festers here. Do you want to search it? Y/N
It looks as though some poor fool has already scoured it for "goodies".
UGH! After scouring through the tree dung and half eaten adventurer's corpses you find.... an Iron Helm!
As you pass through the corridor you overhear two timeworn trees chortling as they share pollination stories.
You see words carved into the wall here: I am imagination, the thing that you think but cannot see.
A group of tree people are deep in discussion, but hush down as you walk by. You hear one grumble "Fleshlings, Disgusting!" with great disdain.

block.field: The small shop has been covered with rocks to simulate a dungeon. There is an astute looking undead gentleman behind an fine gnome crafted glass counter with various wonders inside. Approach the, uh, proprietor? Y/N
You take the stone hand from your pack and place it on the counter. The man's one good eye widens and he cracks a smile.
"Wow, my ad said help wanted not NEED A HAND! HAHA, geez was this guy was heavy handed or what?! This is, hands down, a valuable relic to find! Uhahha! No really, seriously, this is a big deal, ok?"

"This is a hand from a fabled statue of the giant Hewdrus. I got bad news for you, this statue can only be found on the ISLAND of woes. And if you think that name's depressing, the dungeon there is called the Dark Depths!"

"A real ray of sunshine that place is! Ha! Now go to the town of Seaside, by Castle Yrral. The, (cough) "KING's" ship can take you to the ISLAND. Be careful and if you need a HAND you know where to find me!"
"Good daaay" the rotting man says with delight, "When have an odd atrifact bring it by,OK?"
"Well then, thanks for stopping by, don't be a stranger, STRANGER! ahahhaa", he says with a wink of his lashless eye.
To the west is a shop where a small garden of dead flowers has been arranged before it. Above the door a sign covered in confetti and glitter reads "Tip's Antiques of the Ancient World"
The outdoor armor shop has a few new sets of armor on the rack for sale. "Can I tempt you with a new set of Plate Mail and Chain Pants for 1000 Gold?" Y/N
"Very well, they are yours sire!" He hapilly takes your gold and gives you the armor.
"Sorry sire, you lack the coin count for this purchase. Please come back when you do, my apologies!" He sighs and politely shows you to the door.
You are at the edge of the wilderness, leave town? Y/N
The town healer is an older mage woman in emerald robes. "Are you in need of healing? I can heal you for 50 gold, shall I proceed?" She waits for your response. Y/N
"Be still," She says with a smile "This may hurt..." She claps her hands and glorious blinding green healing light fills the space. When your vision returns you are outside.
"Sorry , I don't work for free, mate." She says with a playful wink.
"Perhaps you'd like to buy a Healing Orb for 100 gold instead?" Y/N
"Here is your orb, use it in good health adventurer!"
"Sorry, these don't grow on trees, mate." She says with a playful wink.
You hear a soft voice sing a soothing lullaby from the healers shop next to you.
The shop is ancient and the mage running it is just as old! He says, "Would you like to buy a Lightning Wand for 2500 gold?" Y/N
"Enjoy, it is quite a wand!" The old mage says with a gleam in his eye.
"No gold, no wand, beat it!" He not pleased.
Tog's Tavern is bursting with patrons! A sign behind the bar says, "Spill a beer, eat a spear." Whateva' works! Talk to Tog? Y/N
Tog's a boisterous fellow with a contagious grin. He nods at you as you approach and asks quickly, "Whatdayahave?"
"A good choice, but I like Ale best." Tog serves you your drink.
"A good choice, but I like Ale best." Tog serves you your drink.
Tog serves you your drink. He then adds, "Now that's a real drink! Did you know you can buy Healing Orbs from our healer? Just say no to healing 1st." He says with a wink."
"Sorry, we are fresh out of, uh, That...yeah", and with that you decide to step outside.
The dark and musky weapons shop is stocked with thousands of the same sword. The owner, a gnome, appears to be perfecting his latest copy. "Buy a Elvish Sword for 1000 Gold?" Y/N
"You won't be disappointed! I guarantee it will slice a kobold's head off in one hit or my name isn't Herbert!"
"Hey, hey, hey! Do I look like a run of the mill bridge troll?! Scram until you can pay up bub!"
A sword shaped sign says "Weapons Shop" on the blue building to the north.
A shiny silver shield says "Armor Shop" on the blue building to the east.
You hear the murmur of several people coming from the blue building next to you. You smell...beer?
The cobblestone streets are clean, for the most part. Despite the chaos of the clashing of warriors & thieves in the streets, there are no monsters here.
The hairs on your arm rise with static electricity from the magic shop next to you.

block.field: The door here has text of a long forgotten language on it. Enter? Y/N
The once powerful sorceress' throne room is now empty.
You slowly open the ancient door. Air flows past you quickly as if the chamber had been sealed for centuries. A mysterious glow comes from the room above. You cautiously walk up the remaining stairs.
The Sorceress Queen sits in an onyx throne with her pet lion cub by her side. "Who disturbs my chamber?!" She laughs and says, "Fools, who came to DIE!"
"Noooo!" the sorceress gasps, "I was to live forever and watch Yrral and Zandra suffer for eternity!" Blood flows from her mouth and out of the countess wounds.
Her body is surrounded by a black mist that quickly dissolves her body until only black ash is left.
You carefully step one foot onto the ash to make sure nothing remains of her. You discover Thaedra's ring! You dust off the black ash and take it with you.

block.field: The armor shop is nearly empty. A skinny man in "roomy" armor stands at the wooden counter. "You in the market for a Leather set of pants & jacket? $200 Gold?" Buy it? Y/N
"Here you go kid, no refunds! Now beat it!" He then sits in his chair, leans back and puts his feet up on his desk for some shut-eye.
"Sorry bub, you aynt got the gold!", he shows you the door.
A tattered cloth banner saying "Armor" flies above the entrance of this blue shop next to you.
The inhabitants are out, thanks to you! (press any key)
A foul stench has settled in to the village and the streets are filled with all manner of vile creatures. The town is slowly succumbing to the evils sweeping the land...
You are at the edge the small village, leave? Y/N
The town healer is a beautiful mage in emerald robes. "Are you in need of healing? I can heal you for 25 gold, shall I proceed?" She waits for your response. Y/N
"Very well," She says with a smile "This may tickle..." She claps her hands and glorious blinding blue healing light fills the space. When you vision returns you are outside.
"Sorry Love, no free rides." She says with a playful wink.
The smell of sage burning wafts from the healer's shop next to you.
Static electricity fills the space here. You hear the crackle of lightning from a building next to you.
The magic shop is new, packed with ancient books and new alike. A young mage in green robes asks, "Would you like to buy a Fire Wand for 1000 Gold?" Y/N
"Use it for right, and never might, yes?" The mage offers with a friendly nod.
"Kind adventurer, you lack the coin needed for this transaction. So sorry." The mage gives a shrug.
You enter the small, smoky tavern to find a solemn crowd of patrons. Almost no one is talking to anyone else. The barkeep avoids eye contact. Speak to the barkeep? Y/N
He sees your family amulet and says. "Seek Rhutgaard to the north. They know of the LEGENDS that caused the fall of the old kingdom. Be warned dark creatures live there!"
The weapons shop is sparse at best, business hasn't been good. A thin man in rusty armor says, "We are having a, uh, special on a Dragon Saber for 500 Gold." Buy it Y/N?
"Excellent, come again!" He then returns to counting the coins.
"Whoa, momma didn't raise no fools. Come back when you have the coin!" He motions you to the door.
A small shrine dedicated to the local deity is well kept here. A small plaque reads, "Ellehcim, Goddess of Nature." Flowers and other small offerings litter the ground tastefully.
SQUISH! The smell of vomit hits you almost as fast as the sensation from between your toes. Something has lost its lunch here recently. There are footsteps going to the south...
People of the village take turns fetching water from the life giving natural spring here in the center of town.
A tattered cloth banner saying "Weapons" flies above the entrance of this shop.

block.field: A giant throne made from obsidian ore rests here. What must be Korak's face has been chiseled into the front of it. Various sacrifices and offerings are placed in the seat of the piece.
You enter a great chamber under the volcano and find strange robed people gathered in deep meditation here. One stands slowly and turns to you and says, "Whose Truth do you seek?"
The robed being steps aside and says, "Yes, you ARE a true believer! Please, come forward and join us..."
"I am sorry, only TRUE believers may pass...", the robed being then motions towards the volcano's entrance.
Ancient carvings on the north wall depict a fire god coming to the surface from deep within the underworld. People begin to worship the beast like god.
The next image shows the fire god is ignored by the woman as she gazes at a prince.
A more recently carved scene shows the fire god meeting a powerful sorceress and falling in love.
A freshly carved engraving seems to depict the fire god returning to the underworld in mourning.
Ancient carvings depict the fire god doing battle with the prince and being driven back to this volcano in defeat.

The interior of the volcano is surprisingly hollow. You notice that the walls here have been bored out by some massive beast. The ground glows an eerie purple, illuminating the volcanic rock walls from below.
Cool air washes over you from the outside. Leave the volcano? Y/N
Heat radiating from the pool of lava is almost unbearable!
The boiling pit of magma stirs no longer. You notice a narrow passage leading somewhere. Take it? Y/N
You manage to jump down through a narrow opening to a lower ledge in the main hall. There is no way back up from here.
The fiery pool of red hot magma stirs as if it were mere water as something just below the surface gets closer to you. Suddenly, a massive creature breaks the surface!
"Who disturbs ME?!" Korak lunges at you!
The beast burps up black blood and says in bubble filled voice, "Thaedra!" it gasps,"Now, I return to the dark depths..." he is dead. You find a stone hand in his bloody innards.
You see a strange glowing vapor leave Korak's body and it enters your lungs. You feel strangely stronger and healthier!
Worshippers sit in near silence, with nothing but a rhythmic whispered chant of "Korak, Korak, Korak, Korak... "
HOT LAVA!! Ooh it burns, it BURNS!
This area seems to be far less traveled.
An ancient statue of a giant twisted creature with a huge mouth is blackened by eons of fire here. There is a piece missing where the figure's amulet once was.
The statue glows bright until you are blinded with white light! You feel reality... shifting?
You find an old chest here. Open it? Y/N
You open the old chest and find a bunch of torn, bloody cloth. After rummaging through it all you find...a pair of Iron Gloves!
You have found a petrified wood chest. Open it? Y/N
The chest has already been looted.
You crack open the old chest to find...an Ice Wand!
Many hieroglyphics have been recently added to these halls. They seem to repeat, worshiping a god of the underworld. Their scale implies they were made by humans or other small beings of the realm.
The wall to the north looks like it once was open but has long since been collapsed. Tons of raw ore block the passage. You'll have to find another way through...
You see a deranged man in robes muttering to himself. He says "I know the HOLE truth! YES, holes are weightless! One can put a hole in a bucket, and I'll make it lighter. Like magic!"
This area looks like it was carved out by humans.
Leave the old corridor back into the main chamber? Y/N
